<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="457" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,319]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">Remarks.</emphasis>
This crab has a wide distribution on the Eastern tropical Pacific coast from the Gulf of California to the Galápagos Islands (Brusca 
<number box="[516,576,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="1980.0">1980</number>
). Certainly uncommon in the Gulf, most records in the Mexican tropical Pacific waters come from the Huatulco region (Ramírez-Luna 
<emphasis box="[878,937,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="457">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[947,1006,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="2002.0">2002</number>
, García-Madrigal &amp; Andréu-Sánchez 
<number box="[151,212,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="457" value="2009.0">2009</number>
). In our study, we recorded this species at several sites along the study area and confirm its presence in Mexican waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
